  <prompt>
    Build `InvoiceExtractionToolHandler` — an LLM-assisted `IToolHandler` implementation
    per FR-19 that performs invoice extraction with line-item arithmetic. Pipeline:
    input invoice text/document → LLM structured-output call → extracted line items
    (description, quantity, unit price, tax rate, discount rate) + invoice header
    (vendor, invoice number, date, due date, currency) → deterministic line-item
    arithmetic (line subtotal, line tax, line discount, line total; invoice subtotal,
    total tax, total discount, grand total) → structured `ToolResult`.

    Tax + discount handling: per-line tax/discount rates configurable; tax computation
    method configurable (inclusive vs exclusive); discount application order configurable
    (pre-tax vs post-tax). All math uses `decimal`.

    Configurable via `sprk_analysistool.sprk_configuration`: `taxMethod` (inclusive /
    exclusive), `discountOrder` (pre-tax / post-tax), `roundingMode`, `decimalPrecision`,
    `expectedCurrencies`, `modelDeployment` override.

    Handler registers via auto-discovery per task 100 — implements `IToolHandler`;
    `HandlerId = "InvoiceExtractionToolHandler"`; lives in
    `Services/Ai/Handlers/InvoiceExtractionToolHandler.cs`. Requires `sprk_analysistool`
    row with `sprk_handlerclass = "InvoiceExtractionToolHandler"`.

    LLM call uses structured outputs; per-tenant cache (ADR-014); rate limit (ADR-016);
    safety pipeline (NFR-13).

    Tests use mocked `IOpenAiClient`. Cover: contract test + positive (mocked LLM
    returns invoice → arithmetic correct for inclusive + exclusive tax modes + discount
    orderings) + error (negative quantity, missing currency, LLM invalid JSON) +
    config-driven (tax method swap → different line totals) + cache + arithmetic
    determinism (same line items → same totals across 100 runs).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with .NET 8 + Azure OpenAI structured-outputs + invoice/billing
    domain experience. Comfortable with `decimal` arithmetic, tax-inclusive vs exclusive
    semantics, discount application order edge cases.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `InvoiceExtractionToolHandler.cs` implemented in `Services/Ai/Handlers/`;
    auto-discovered; `sprk_analysistool` row deployed; unit tests cover positive + error
    + config-driven + cache + determinism cases; all arithmetic uses `decimal`; LLM call
    respects cache (ADR-014) + rate limit (ADR-016) + safety pipeline (NFR-13); BFF
    publish-size delta ≤+0.6 MB; `code-review` + `adr-check` green.
  </goal>

