  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context. If &gt;70%, run `context-handoff` then `/compact`. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: New LLM-assisted handler; invoice arithmetic correctness; ADR-013/014/016 + NFR-13; FR-19
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: all 11 steps below including Step 9.5 quality gates
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read TASK-INDEX; confirm 108 is 🔲; dependency 104 complete.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every &lt;inputs&gt; + &lt;knowledge&gt; file.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Design Handler Surface + Output Schema">
      Define `HandlerId = "InvoiceExtractionToolHandler"`; LLM output schema (invoice
      header + line items array); `ConfigSchema` with `taxMethod`, `discountOrder`,
      `roundingMode`, `decimalPrecision`, `expectedCurrencies`. Inject LLM client +
      cache + resolver.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Handler">
      Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/InvoiceExtractionToolHandler.cs`.
      Pattern: validate input → check per-tenant cache → on miss, call LLM via structured
      outputs → validate JSON shape → execute deterministic line-item arithmetic per
      configured tax method + discount order using `decimal` → emit `ToolResult` with
      structured invoice. Telemetry per ADR-015 (no invoice content in logs).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author Unit Tests">
      Create `InvoiceExtractionToolHandlerTests.cs` using `TypedToolHandlerTestFixture`.
      Mock `IOpenAiClient`. Cover: contract; positive (mocked LLM returns invoice → math
      correct for both inclusive + exclusive tax + both discount orderings — at least 4
      combinations); error (negative qty, missing currency, LLM invalid JSON); config-driven
      (tax method swap shifts totals deterministically); cache (second call hits cache);
      arithmetic determinism (same line items + same config → same totals across 100
      runs); telemetry (no invoice content in logs).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Seed sprk_analysistool Row">
      Create `infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-invoice-extraction-row.json` with
      `sprk_handlerclass = "InvoiceExtractionToolHandler"`, `sprk_toolcode = "INV-EXTRACT@v1"`,
      sample `sprk_configuration`, `AvailableInContexts = "Both"`. Deploy to Spaarke
      Dev. Capture evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Build + Tests + Vuln Check">
      `dotnet build` + `dotnet test --filter "InvoiceExtractionToolHandler"`. Vuln check.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify BFF Publish-Size Delta">
      `dotnet publish -c Release ...`. Report absolute + diff. Target ≤+0.6 MB.
      Cumulative Wave 1 + Wave 2 delta MUST be ≤+5 MB per spec NFR-02; record in task
      notes.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through criteria; record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` + `adr-check`. Both MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update status `complete`; TASK-INDEX 108 🔲 → ✅; reset `current-task.md`. Note in
      task-108-deployment-evidence.md that Wave 2 is now complete and task 109 (dispatch
      test) is unblocked.
    </step>
  </steps>

